OL,3,CSupreme Court to issue ruling in
OL,4,Cdispute over definition of a woman
OL,6,FThe dispute centres on whether or not
OL,7,Fsomebody with a gender recognition
OL,8,Fcertificate (GRC) recognising their
OL,9,Fgender as female should be treated as
OL,10,Fa woman under the 2010 Equality Act.
OL,12,FFWS previously said that not tying the
OL,13,Fdefinition of sex to its "ordinary
OL,14,Fmeaning" could have far-reaching
OL,15,Fconsequences for sex-based rights, as
OL,16,Fwell as "everyday single-sex services"
OL,17,Flike toilets and hospital wards.
