OL,3,CSupreme Court to issue ruling in
OL,4,Cdispute over definition of a woman
OL,6,FThe matter first came to court in
OL,7,F2022, when FWS successfully challenged
OL,8,Fthe Gender Representation on Public
OL,9,FBoards (Scotland) Act 2018 over its
OL,10,Finclusion of trans women in its
OL,11,Fdefinition of women.
OL,13,FThe Court of Session ruled that
OL,14,Fchanging the definition of a woman in
OL,15,Fthe act was unlawful, as it dealt with
OL,16,Fmatters falling outside the Scottish
OL,17,FParliament's legal competence.
