OL,3,CSupreme Court to issue ruling in
OL,4,Cdispute over definition of a woman
OL,6,F"Trans rights are protected under the
OL,7,Fseparate category of gender
OL,8,Freassignment but, to fully guarantee
OL,9,Fwomen's rights, it is increasingly
OL,10,Fclear that a consistent, biological
OL,11,Fand factual understanding of sex is
OL,12,Fthe only workable solution."
OL,14,FDuring the hearing, Ruth Crawford KC,
OL,15,Frepresenting the Scottish Government,
OL,16,Fsaid a GRC affected a "change in legal
OL,17,Fstatus", and that someone with a GRC
OL,18,F"becomes recognised as belonging to,
OL,19,For becoming, the sex of their acquired
OL,20,Fgender".
